solutions.content:

	Consider the given example:  s1= aabcc  s2 = dbbca  s3=  aa dbbc bc a c

	We start with an empty s3, adding characters one by one and finding if we can use some substring of s1 and s2  to construct this s3.
	Using a 2D vector to store the answers along the way.
	dp[i][j] = true if it is possible to construct the string s3[0....i+j-1] using substrings s1[0...i-1]  and s2[0...j-1]


1.  Base case : dp[0][0] = true
	 Since we can make an empty string s3  from 2 empty strings s1 and s2.

2.	 When one of the strings is empty

		When s2 is empty
		Add characters one by one to s3 and s1 while keeping s2 empty.		
		eg.             s1 = "a"  s2 = " "    s3 = "a".    We can make s3 using this s1 and s2. 
		   Therefore, dp[1][0] = true  since s3[0] = s2[0] 

		To find dp[i][0],
		we just check whether the last charcter of s3 is same as last char of s1 , s3[i-1] == s1[i-1] and
		if it is possible to construct the string, s3 minus current character
		i.e.  dp[i-1][0] is true.
			This way we have filled the first column of our dp. 

				dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][0]  and (s3[i-1] == s1[i-1])
		Similarly  we can fill the first row when s1 is empty and s2 is not.

			dp[0][j] = (s3[j-1] == s2[j-1] ) and dp[0][j-1]


3.	Now consider the case when both strings are not empty.

	 eg. to find dp[1][1]
		 s1 = "a"  s2 = "d"    s3 = "aa"


	  We need to check 2 conditions : 
	a. whether the last character of s3 is same as last characters of either s1 or s2. 
		If  not same then its not possible to make s3.

	b. whether it's possible to construct the string s3 minus current character.
			i.e  when s3 has a single character. Those are dp[0][1] and dp[1][0] .


	If the last character of s3 comes from s1, 
	then check whether it is possible to construct the string s3 minus current character using   substring s2 and substring s1 minus last character.
`bool t1 = (s3[i+j-1] == s1[i-1] ) and dp[i-1][j];`

	Similarly if the last character of s3 comes from s2,
		`bool t2 = (s3[i+j-1] == s2[j-1]) and dp[i][j-1];`



 If either of t1 or t2 is true then we can make s3 with current substrings s1 and s2.





```
bool isInterleave(string s1, string s2, string s3) {
        int m= s1.length(), n= s2.length();
        if(s3.length() != m+n) return false;
        vector<vector<bool>> dp(m+1,vector<bool>(n+1,false));

        dp[0][0]  = 1;

        for(int i=1; i<=m;i++)
            dp[i][0] = (s3[i-1] == s1[i-1]) and dp[i-1][0];

        for(int j=1;j<=n; j++)
            dp[0][j] = (s3[j-1] == s2[j-1]) and dp[0][j-1];

        for(int i=1;i<=m;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<=n;j++){
                bool t1 = (s3[i+j-1] == s1[i-1] ) and dp[i-1][j];
                bool t2 = (s3[i+j-1] == s2[j-1]) and dp[i][j-1];
                dp[i][j] = t1 or t2;
            }
        }

        return dp[m][n];


    }
