3. Rest of the Cells

* **First Cell** -> meaning  0 characters of s1 and 0 characters of s2 interleave to form 0 characters of s3 
		![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/2e489f60-ac5d-46a6-b3b4-4812f788e547_1631866807.4218714.png)

* **First Row** -> When  s1 is empty and s2 is not empty , then we have to check if substring of s2 = substring of s3
   ```
    if (s2[i-1] != s3[i-1])
		dp[0][i] = false;
	else 
		dp[0][i] = dp[0][i-1];
   ```
  **Remember** : If we are at cell(i,j), then current characters of s1, s2 and s3 are (i-1)th, (j-1)th and (i+j-1)th characters of s1 , s2 and s3 respectively.

  Similarly ,
  **First Column** -> When s2 is empty and s1 is not empty, then we have to check if substring of s1 = substring of s3
  ```
	  if(s1[i-1] != s3[i-1])
	     dp[i][0] = false;
	  else 
		  dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][0];
  ```
  ![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/1c91c32c-c60f-4dfb-9e19-d785058dc61c_1631868477.9101102.png)


*   **Rest of the cells**
  We have 4 possiblities for the rest of the cells, If
	  1. Current character of s3 is neither equals to current character of s1 nor current character of s2, then value of the cell is false
	  2. Current character of s3 is equal  current character of s1 but not current character of s2, then value of cell is the same cell above it.
	3. Current character of s3 is equal to current character of s2 but not current character of s1 , then value of cell is the cell left to it.
	4. Current character of s3 is equal to current character of s2 and current character of s1 , then value of cell is either from cell above it or cell left to it if they are true, otherwise false

		![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/fe18ed45-fe8c-4f54-bbda-8c4b74b277da_1631869257.556291.png)

```
class Solution {
public:
    bool isInterleave(string s1, string s2, string s3) {
        int n = s1.size();
        int m = s2.size();
        int l = s3.size();

        if(l != n + m)return false;

        vector<vector<bool>> dp(n+1 , vector<bool>(m+1, false));

        dp[0][0] = true;

        //populating first row
        for(int i=1 ;i<=m ;i++){
            if(s2[i-1] != s3[i-1])dp[0][i] = false;
            else dp[0][i] = dp[0][i-1];
        }

        //populating first col
        for(int i=1 ;i<=n ;i++){
            if(s1[i-1] != s3[i-1])dp[i][0] = false;
            else dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][0];
        }

        // rest
        for(int i=1;i<=n ;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<=m ;j++){
                if(s1[i-1] == s3[i+j-1] and s2[j-1] == s3[i+j-1]){
                    dp[i][j] = (dp[i-1][j] || dp[i][j-1]);
                }
                else if(s1[i-1] == s3[i+j-1] and s2[j-1] != s3[i+j-1]){
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j];
                } 
                else if(s1[i-1] != s3[i+j-1] and s2[j-1] == s3[i+j-1]){
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i][j-1];
                }else{
                    dp[i][j] = false;
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[n][m];



    }
};

```

Time : O(M*N)

Space : O(M*N)

**Space Opitmization**
**Idea** : To fill the each row , we just need one row above it ( 2 rows at a time ) 

```
