solutions.content:
While solving dp question always first find what are the possible choices you have at any given point i.e., first make the choice diagram and then coding it will be very easy.

And if you see some overlapping sub problems then just store their result and use it later.

In this question, we have to form `s3` using `s1` and `s2` while maintaining their orders.

## How we're getting the answer

In the given test case:

s1 = `aabcc`
s2 = `dbbca`
s3 = `aadbbcbcac`

I'm starting from the end and trying to make `s3` with the help of `s1` and `s2`

Let `i = s1.size() - 1` (end of `s1`) and `j = s2.size() - 1` (end of `s2`) and `k = s3.size() - 1` (end of `s3`)

1. First I need `c`, so take `c` from `s1` (now `s1` = `aabc ` and s2 =`dbbca` and `s3` = `aadbbcbca`)
2. Now,  I need `a`, so take `a` from `s2` (now `s1` = `aabc ` and s2 =`dbbc` and `s3` = `aadbbcbc`)
3. Now, I need `c`, so I can take `c` from either `s1` or from `s2`

This intuition is more than enough to make the choice diagram

## Choice Diagram

1. `ith` character of `s1` = `kth` character of `s3`  (aabc**c**, aadbbcbca**c**)

	Just shift the two pointers `i` to `i-1` and `k` to `k-1` as we've included `c` from `s1`

	```
	solve(s1, s2, s3, i-1, j, k-1);
	```

2. `jth` character of `s2` = `kth` character of `s3`  (dbbc**a**, aadbbcbc**a**)

	Just shift the two pointers `j` to `j-1` and `k` to `k-1`

	```
	solve(s1, s2, s3, i, j-1, k-1);
	```

3. Both `ith` and `jth` character are equal to `kth` character of `s3` (aab**c**, dbb**c**, aadbbcb**c**)

	In this case I can take the character from any of the string. And since I can get answer from any of the possiblity that's why I'm using `||` 

	```
	solve(s1, s2, s3, i-1, j, k-1) || solve(s1, s2,s3, i, j-1, k-1);
	```


4. None of them are equal to `kth` character of `s3`
	If none of the character is equal to the `kth` character of `s3` then it's impossible to make `s3` with the help of `s1` and `s2` as they don't contain the `kth` character in them.

## Recursive Code

In this step we just have to code the choice diagram

```
bool solve(string &s1, string &s2, string &s3, int i, int j, int k)
{

	// Base Case
	if(k == 0 and (i or j)) // If we've reached the end of s3 but still some of the characters are remaining in s1 or s2 then return false as we've to utilise every character of s1 and s2
		return false;

	if(i == 0 and j == 0 and k == 0) // If we've exhausted all of the three strings then just return true as we have finally formed s3 with the help of s1 and s2
		return true;

	// Choice Diagram

	// i and j should be > 0, which make sures that there are some characters left in our string

	if(i > 0 and j > 0 and s1[i-1] == s2[j-1] and s1[i-1] == s3[k-1]) // Case 3
		return solve(s1, s2, s3, i-1, j, k-1) || solve(s1, s2,s3, i, j-1, k-1);

	if(i > 0 and s3[k-1] == s1[i-1]) // Case 1
		return solve(s1, s2, s3, i-1, j, k-1);

	if(j > 0 and s3[k-1] == s2[j-1]) // Case 2
		return solve(s1, s2,s3, i, j-1, k-1);

	return false; // Case 4
}

bool isInterleave(string s1, string s2, string s3) {

	if(s1.size() + s2.size() != s3.size())
		return false;

	return solve(s1, s2, s3, s1.size(), s2.size(), s3.size());
}
```

## Memoized Code

We just have to add 2-3 extra lines to convert recusive code into memoized code. Make a DP Table and store the subproblems result in it.

```
bool solve(string &s1, string &s2, string &s3, int i, int j, int k, vector<vector<int>> &dp)
{
	if(k == 0 and (i or j))
		return false;

	if(i == 0 and j == 0 and k == 0)
		return true;

	if(dp[i][j] != -1) // Just return the result from the cache
		return dp[i][j];

	if(i > 0 and j > 0 and s1[i-1] == s2[j-1] and s1[i-1] == s3[k-1])
		return dp[i][j] = solve(s1, s2, s3, i-1, j, k-1, dp) || solve(s1, s2,s3, i, j-1, k-1, dp); // before returning the result store it into the cache

	if(i > 0 and s3[k-1] == s1[i-1])
		return dp[i][j] = solve(s1, s2, s3, i-1, j, k-1, dp);

	if(j > 0 and s3[k-1] == s2[j-1])
		return dp[i][j] = solve(s1, s2,s3, i, j-1, k-1, dp);

	return dp[i][j] = false;
}

bool isInterleave(string s1, string s2, string s3) {

	vector<vector<int>> dp(s1.size() + 1, vector<int> (s2.size() + 1, -1)); // initialisiation of 2D vector

	if(s1.size() + s2.size() != s3.size())
		return false;

	return solve(s1, s2, s3, s1.size(), s2.size(), s3.size(), dp);
}
```

Small tip to avoid TLE 

Always use call by referance wherever you can as in call by referance you're not wasting any time in making copies of variables in every function call.

So, if I've used `bool solve(string s1, string s2, string s3, int i, int j, int k, vector<vector<int>> dp)` this instead of `bool solve(string &s1, string &s2, string &s3, int i, int j, int k, vector<vector<int>> &dp)` then I would've definately gotten TLE as I'm unncecessarily copying the values in every function call.

